# KonnexCore — environment variable template.
#
# Copy this file to `.env` for local development. Variables prefixed
# with `KONNEXCORE_` are loaded by `core.config.Settings` via
# pydantic-settings.
#
# Fail-secure policy (per the `insecure-defaults` skill): any variable
# that is REQUIRED for production must be declared without a default
# in `core/config.py` so the application crashes at startup if it is
# missing, instead of silently running with an insecure fallback.
#
# Phase 0 has no required variables. Future phases will add entries
# below as their fail-secure surface grows.

# Optional: override the public version string returned by /api/health.
# KONNEXCORE_APP_VERSION=0.1.0

# Phase 3 (LLM compare) — optional. If unset, /api/verify/with-llm-compare
# returns a 503 instead of falling back to a default key.
# KONNEXCORE_OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Phase 8 (deployment) — public CORS allowlist. Comma-separated origins.
# KONNEXCORE_CORS_ORIGINS=https://your-domain.example
